tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose regulation or possible prediabetes. Total cholesterol and HDL are slightly above the reference range, while LDL and triglycerides are within normal limits. Renal function, electrolytes, and other parameters are unremarkable. Recommend clinical correlation for cardiovascular risk and glycemic control, with consideration of lifestyle modification and follow-up.
